title: Mexico arrested cartel suspects. Thousands besieged a state capital.
description: The violence in Chilpancingo, the capital of Guerrero state, was an unusually stark challenge by an organized crime group to a government attempt to enforce criminal laws.

title: Johannesburg sees first snow in a decade
description: Though some parts of South Africa normally see snow, the last recorded snowfall in Johannesburg was in 2012.

title: Four maps explain how Sweden and Finland could alter NATO’s security
description: The countries also offer key geographic advantages, which would enhance NATO’s defenses.

title: Zelensky slams NATO over no clear path to membership, despite Biden unity pitch
description: Volodymyr Zelensky said NATO’s leaders weren’t serious about inviting Ukraine to the alliance and were using membership as a future negotiating tactic with Russia.

title: Volcano erupts near Iceland’s capital, in photos and videos
description: Thousands of small earthquakes were recorded in the days before the eruption close to Litli Hrutur, around 20 miles from Iceland’s capital Reykjavik.

title: Israeli protests return as Netanyahu restarts judicial overhaul
description: After the ruling coalition passed a first reading of the measure to limit the Supreme Court's power, protest organizers pledged a “day of disruption."

title: Canada has wildfires every year. Why won’t it create a firefighting force?
description: The worst wildfire season on record has challenged the provincial firefighting resources on which the country relies.

title: Man compared to Ted Bundy arrested in killing of Tijuana sex worker
description: U.S. Marshals arrested Bryant Rivera, a California man accused of killing sex workers in Tijuana. Mexican authorities have called him a serial killer.

title: Russia-Ukraine war live updates: Ukraine tops NATO summit agenda after Turkey backs Sweden’s membership
description: The summit is a show of Western unity against Russia — but there are divisions over Kyiv’s candidacy and the U.S. decision to supply it with cluster munitions.

title: As NATO summit begins, Lithuania struts big on world stage
description: As NATO member states gather to affirm Sweden’s accession and discuss Ukraine’s way forward, the small host country may have a big role with bigger expectations.
